about_the_job:
As a Service Delivery Model and System of Care Specialist, you will be responsible for:
Compliance with Ministry of Health Regulations and Rules:
Stay updated on the latest rules, regulations, and guidelines issued by the Ministry of Health;
Collaborate with the client's Primary Healthcare to ensure strict adherence to all regulatory requirements;
Conduct regular audits and assessments to verify compliance and address any issues promptly.
Service Delivery Model Development:
Work closely with healthcare providers to design and implement patient-centered care delivery models that align with Ministry of Health guidelines and the global standard set by WHO;
Develop standardized care protocols and best practices that meet regulatory requirements while optimizing patient care;
Identify opportunities for innovation and improvement in service delivery to meet regulatory standards and WHO guidelines.
Healthcare System Optimization:
Assess and enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of healthcare systems, ensuring compliance with Ministry of Health standards and WHO global standards;
Collaborate with relevant stakeholders to streamline healthcare processes, reduce administrative burdens, and ensure regulatory compliance;
Implement measures to simplify healthcare system workflows in alignment with WHO recommendations.
Quality Assurance and Improvement:
Establish and monitor key performance indicators (KPIs) aligned with Ministry of Health requirements and WHO global standards to ensure high-quality healthcare service delivery;
Lead continuous quality improvement initiatives to enhance patient outcomes and satisfaction per WHO guidelines;
Regularly conduct audits and assessments to maintain and improve service quality.
Training and Capacity Building:
Provide training and capacity-building support to healthcare staff on complying with Ministry of Health regulations, standards, and best practices, and WHO global standards;
Promote a culture of continuous learning and professional development within the unit, incorporating WHO-recommended practices.
Patient Engagement and Satisfaction:
Develop strategies to enhance patient engagement, communication, and feedback mechanisms, all while adhering to Ministry of Health guidelines and WHO standards;
Monitor patient satisfaction and implement measures to address concerns and improve the patient experience in compliance with WHO recommendations.
Innovation and Best Practices:
Drive innovation in healthcare service delivery to improve effectiveness and efficiency, aligning with WHO global standards;
Collaborate with healthcare teams to identify and implement best practices that adhere to WHO guidelines for healthcare service delivery.
Collaboration with Stakeholders:
Collaborate closely with internal teams, government agencies, NGOs, and other partners to ensure effective service delivery while complying with Ministry of Health regulations and WHO global standards;
Represent the client's Primary Healthcare in discussions related to regulatory compliance, healthcare innovation, and adherence to WHO recommendations.
Gender, Social, and Environmental Assessment:
Assess and address the impact of healthcare interventions on gender and social equity;
Evaluate the environmental sustainability of healthcare practices.
Collaboration with Monitoring, Evaluation, and Learning Specialist:
Work closely with the MEL Specialist to ensure effective implementation and assessment of service delivery models;
Utilize data and insights provided by the MEL Specialist for continuous improvement;
Coordinate in developing and refining evaluation methods and tools.

Requirements:
Master's degree in Public Health, Healthcare Management, or a related field;
Proven experience in healthcare compliance and system optimization, preferably in primary healthcare setting;
Strong understanding of Ministry of Health rules, regulations, and quality standards.

